Pre-Game Insights: Ghana will test their strength against Namibia in an International friendly at the Baba Yara Sports stadium on Monday, January 8, 2024 as a preparatory game for the 34th edition of the TotalEnergies Africa Cup of Nations Cote D'Ivoire 2023.
Both teams will use the friendly to draw up a plan for the tournament that kicks off in Abidjan on Saturday, January 13, 2024.
Ghana are placed in Group B alongside Cape Verde, Egypt and Mozambique while Namibia have a date with Tunisia, South Africa and Mali in Group E.
The game is scheduled for 8pm kick off at the Baba Yara Sports stadium.
The public is hereby informed that Centre Line and Popular stand is free of charge.
